        ##### Directions to Todos 
          
        Now there is a wonderful new toll road that bypasses Cabo San Lucas! 
      
      %ol.directions
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-left-turn.svg'
          When exiting the airport, turn left. Look for signage saying <abbr>CUOTA</abbr>.
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-ticket.svg'
          Proceed to the first toll-booth. Press the red button for a printed ticket.
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-fork.svg'
          The first fork in the road you encounter will be for <abbr>SAN JOSE</abbr> or <abbr>CABO</abbr>. Take the <strong><abbr>CABO</abbr></strong> option.
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-fork.svg'
          The next (and last) fork you come to will give you the option of <abbr>CABO</abbr> or <abbr>TODOS SANTOS</abbr>. Take <strong><abbr>TODOS SANTOS</abbr></strong>.
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-money.svg'
          When you reach the tollbooth, relinquish your ticket and pay $70 pesos (or the <abbr>USD</abbr> equivalent).
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-highway-19.svg'
          You will then merge with the main highway <abbr>(MEXICO 19 NORTH)</abbr> and be on your way to Todos Santos.
        %li
          =image_tag 'images/info-to-be-known/directions/directions-right-turn.svg'
          On entering Todos Santos on Calle Degollado: Drive across the stop-light, after stop light turn right onto Calle Juarez. This is the main street with Hotel California.

